=== BT-543 LATTICE SCAN (round 2, lattice angle) ===

=== BT-543 LATTICE VERIFY ===
math primitives self-test:
  sqrt(2) = 1.41421 dev=2.69051e-11
  exp(1)  = 2.71828 dev=4.09544e-11
  ln(2)   = 0.693147 dev=4.0055e-11
  tanh(1) = 0.761594 dev=4.42352e-11
  math PASS: 4/4
=== (A) 2D Z_2 Wilson loop area-law scan ===
  sigma(beta) = -log(tanh(beta))   [DERIVED, Wilson 1974]
  <W(R,T)> = exp(-sigma*R*T)       [DERIVED, area law]

  beta       sigma       W(1,1)     W(2,2)     W(3,3)     fit:R*T*sigma/Area
  0.1   2.30591   0.099668   9.86786e-05   9.70513e-10   2.30591 PASS
  0.3   1.23336   0.291313   0.00720174   1.51089e-05   1.23336 PASS
  0.5   0.771937   0.462117   0.0456046   0.000961101   0.771937 PASS
  0.75   0.453896   0.635149   0.162743   0.0168221   0.453896 PASS
  1   0.272341   0.761594   0.33643   0.086201   0.272341 PASS
  1.5   0.0996565   0.905148   0.671242   0.407828   0.0996565 PASS
  2   0.0366354   0.964028   0.86369   0.719126   0.0366354 PASS
  area-law PASS: 7/7
  NOTE: for small beta, W(R,T) underflows to ~1e-10; -log via analytic
  identity used. Direct ln_(W) Taylor is numerically unstable on tiny W.

=== (B) Static qq-bar potential V(r) ===
  V(r) = lim_{T->inf} -log<W(r,T)>/T = sigma * r  [DERIVED confinement]

  at beta=0.5, sigma=0.771937
  r      V(r)       expected   dev
  1      0.771937   0.771937   0
  2      1.54387   1.54387   0
  3      2.31581   2.31581   0
  4      3.08775   3.08775   0
  5      3.85968   3.85968   0
  linear fit: max_dev=0 PASS
  CONFINEMENT: V linear in r -> 2D Z_2 confines [DERIVED]
  4D analog (Clay): NOT verified by this computation. 2D is solvable; 4D is open.

=== (C) Mass gap via Ising duality (2D Z_2) ===
  Kramers-Wannier: 2D Z_2 gauge <-> 2D Ising
  m_gap(beta) ~ -log(tanh(beta)) in disordered phase (beta < beta_c)
  beta_c(Ising) = (1/2)*log(1+sqrt(2))
  beta_c = 0.440687 (expected 0.44068679)

  beta    m_gap     phase
  0.1   2.30591   disordered gap>0 POSITIVE
  0.2   1.62265   disordered gap>0 POSITIVE
  0.3   1.23336   disordered gap>0 POSITIVE
  0.4   0.967718   disordered gap>0 POSITIVE
  positive mass gaps: 4/4
  2D: gap > 0 in disordered phase [DERIVED]
  4D Clay YM: positivity of gap UNRESOLVED [HONEST_MISS]

=== (D) beta_c self-duality check ===
  beta_c = (1/2)*log(1+sqrt(2)) = 0.440687
  sinh(2*beta_c) = 1 (expected 1.0)
  self-duality dev = 2.22045e-16
  PASS

=== (E) Honesty: 2D vs 4D ===
  Results above VERIFY hexa numerical stack on EXACTLY-SOLVABLE 2D.
  Literature status (BT-543 round 1 CE-1, CE-2):
   - Balaban 1988-89: 2D and 3D continuum YM rigorous.
   - Magnen-Rivasseau-Seneor 1993: 4D partial, conditional on UV cutoff.
   - Chatterjee 2016/2020: 2D stochastic YM.
   - 4D pure YM mass gap: UNRESOLVED (Clay Millennium).
  Hexa primitives sufficient for 2D toy.
  Scaling to 4D lattice requires: (i) SU(N) Haar integration, (ii) Monte Carlo
  heat-bath updater, (iii) finite-size extrapolation. Not attempted here.
  BT-543 conclusion: 0/1 MISS. Numerical 2D toy solvable; 4D Clay not moved.

=== SUMMARY ===
All 2D Z_2 lattice checks reduce to exact closed forms (Wilson 1974,
Wegner 1971, Kramers-Wannier 1941). Hexa primitives validated.
4D SU(3) Clay mass gap remains UNRESOLVED.
